<div class="section-two-ec">
	<div class="intro-ec poem-share">
		“a Milton las paredes de la sombra,
		el destierro a Cervantes y el ovido. 
		Suyo es lo que perdura en la memoria
		del tiempo secular. Nuestra la escoria.”<br><br>
		Borges, El Otro
	</div>
</div>
<div class="poem-ec poem-share">
	<div>
		Swim beneath the vast shadow,<br> 
		and watch the dock disappear. 
	</div>

	<div>
		You will never see Castile’s sunrise<br>
		reach for the night sky – just hear it<br>
		described.
	</div> 

	<div>
		What you call memory is merely<br>
		the sum of colours caught<br> 
		between distant mirrors. 
	</div>
	<div>
		And where there is blackness, you invent<br>
		hues that become more brilliant<br>
		with each reflection. 
	</div>
	<div>
		Milton’s living sapphires fill<br>
		your empty sky. 
	</div>
	<div>
		Stare at the lines or wait for the sun until<br> 
		you go <%= link_to 'blind', '/exile.html', class:"hover-link" %>. 
	</div>
</div>


